:Observatory_Quest\n 19.03%  180.167      1 Template:StoreLine\n 12.25%  116.014      2 Template:Navbox\n 12.22%  115.687      1 Template:Hastranscript\n  8.41%   79.590      1 Template:CitePostbag\n  6.59%   62.416      1 Template:Ctg\n  5.43%   51.427      1 Template:Map\n  5.19%   49.114      1 Template:Reflist\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key en_osrswiki:pcache:idhash:24789-0!dateformat=default and timestamp 20220420163317 and revision id 14260793. Serialized with PHP.\n -->\n</div>","rawContent":"{{External|rs|rsc}}\n{{Infobox NPC\n|name = Spirit of Scorpius\n|image = [[File:Spirit of Scorpius.png|130px]]\n|release = [[17 March]] [[2003]]\n|update = Observatory Quest online!\n|members = Yes\n|race = [[Ghost]]\n|location = [[Grave of Scorpius]], south-west of [[Ardougne]]\n|gender = Male\n|options = Talk-to\n|examine = The essence of evil.\n|map = {{Map|name=Spirit of Scorpius|x=2464|y=3227|r=3|mtype=square}}\n|id = 5371\n}}\n[[File:Spirit of Scorpius chathead.png|left]]\nThe '''Spirit of Scorpius''' is a [[Zamorak]]ian ghost.{{CiteNPC|npc=Astronomy book|quote=Before long, Scorpius used his knowledge for predicting the future, and, in turn, he called upon the dark knowledge of Zamorakian worshippers to further his cause.}} After completion of [[Observatory Quest]], he will give the player an [[unholy mould]] and bless [[unholy symbol]]s. He is found south-west of [[Ardougne]] by the [[Grave of Scorpius]], due north of the [[Observatory]]. An unholy mould '''must''' be claimed from him before he will bless any unholy symbols. He will not give the player an unholy mould if there is one already in their inventory.\n\nScorpius is close to both the [[Red salamander (Hunter)|red salamander]] hunting area and the [[Ourania Cave]].\n\nWhilst alive, Scorpius was an astronomer and had an apprentice named [[Phyrrys]]. It is said that he created the art, and that he has a constellation named after him.{{CitePostbag|author=Reldo|issue=21|letter=Letter 5}}\n\nScorpius was later persecuted for his craft and his knowledge and instruments were almost totally lost.{{CiteNPC|npc=Astronomy book|quote=The kings of that time worked to banish the Zamorakian followers in the area, hiding all reference to Scorpius's invention, due to its 'evil nature'.}} The art eventually returned to the world, as discovered in the [[Observatory Quest]].\n\n==Stock==\n{{StoreTableHead|hidebuy=y|hidecaption=y|hidestock=y|hidege=y|hiderestock=y}}\n{{StoreLine|name=Unholy mould|stock=inf|sell=0|buy=N/A|gemw=n}}\n{{StoreTableBottom}}\n\n==Dialogue==\n{{hastranscript|npc}}\n\n==Changes==\n===Gallery (historical)===\n{|style=\"text-align: center\" cellpadding=\"15\"\n|[[File:Spirit of Scorpius (historical).png|300x150px]]\n|[[File:Spirit of Scorpius.png|300x150px]]\n|-\n|[[File:Spirit of Scorpius chathead (historical).png]]\n|[[File:Spirit of Scorpius chathead.png]]\n|-\n|29 March 2004 –<br/>22 January 2007\n|22 January 2007 –<br/>present\n|}\n\n==Trivia==\n*Though he is a [[ghost]], the player does not need an [[amulet of ghostspeak]] to talk to him. When you do talk to him, the chatbox says, \"This powerful spirit seems capable of speaking to you even though you are not wearing an Amulet of Ghostspeak.\"\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Observatory Quest}}\n[[Category:Zamorakians]]"}